comment:
She has just made so much harder for women who are legitimately abused and victims of domestic abuse to be believed.  Much like the women in the eighties who claimed they were raped, and were proven not to be. It put the whole justice system back forty years. And makes it hard for people to be believed.  As a person who has been raped more than a dozen times, mostly as a child, and later on as a young adult in my early twenties, I can tell you for a fact, that reporting the rapes, never entered into my mind as proving them would have been all but impossible, and stressfull, not to mention emotionally draining.  And I know from having reported my childhood abuse in the late seventies, and early eighties, that I was never believed then. Not by teachers, social workers, and family members. I left me wide open to be victimized again and again. And not just by one offender, I was raped at school event once by the principal of my school on an overnight trip. My father's own boss laid his hands on my privates, and was only stopped by me choosing to go to my abuser's bed instead.  Imagine, being a child, woken up, by a man with his hands down your panties, and they are around your knees.  And the only option for defence is to willingly go to the first abuser that has been doing it for years??  Also a friends father had a go at me one night, as I slept over at her house.  That was unpleasant, but my screaming ended his attempts.  And the final time I recall being raped, was as a 19yo. I was asleep on a friends couch, I was drunk, too drunk to protest. And a man I had told no to on many many occasions decided to have a go at me that night.  As I was trapped, I said nothing and allowed it to happen, and forgot about it until many years later, when "date rape" stories became popular.  I no longer drink, and have since forgiven my abusers, as it is pointless to carry those kinds of weights around with you.  But I haven't forgotten. How awful it was to be called a liar over and over again, when I tried to report them.

What this woman has done, is made liars out of real vicitms again.  And she should be locked up on account of her lies. She should have to repay all the money ever given to her by Johnny, and also be made to pay for his lost wages, from Warner Bros, firing him from his role as Grindlewald, as a direct result of her lies.  Furthermore, if they make a fourth film, then she should have to pay JD for his lost wages from that future film as well.  And until she has repaid that, she should lose her SAG card, and not be allowed to work in Films again.
